### Variables
@host = http://localhost:3000
@api = {{host}}/api

### ====================================
### AUTENTICACIÓN - LOGIN
### ====================================

### 1. Registrar nuevo usuario
POST {{api}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "first_name": "Juan",
  "last_name": "Pérez",
  "email": "juan.perez@example.com"
}

### 2. Login con credenciales
POST {{api}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "juan.perez@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### 3. Renovar token con Refresh Token
### (Reemplaza tu_refresh_token con el token obtenido del login)
POST {{api}}/auth/refresh-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "tu_refresh_token"
}

### 4. Logout
POST {{api}}/auth/logout
Content-Type: application/json

### 5. Cambiar contraseña temporal
### (Requiere token de autenticación)
POST {{api}}/auth/change-temporary-password
Authorization: Bearer tu_token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "newPassword": "NuevaPassword123!",
  "confirmPassword": "NuevaPassword123!"
}

### 6. Solicitar restablecimiento de contraseña
POST {{api}}/auth/request-password-reset
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "juan.perez@example.com"
}

### ====================================
### USUARIOS - Rutas protegidas
### ====================================

### Obtener todos los usuarios (requiere token)
GET {{api}}/users
Authorization: Bearer tu_token

### Obtener usuario por ID (requiere token)
GET {{api}}/users/1
Authorization: Bearer tu_token

### Actualizar usuario (requiere token)
PUT {{api}}/users/1
Authorization: Bearer tu_token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "first_name": "Juan",
  "last_name": "Pérez Actualizado",
  "email": "juan.nuevo@example.com",
  "phone": "1234567890"
}

### Eliminar usuario (requiere token)
DELETE {{api}}/users/1
Authorization: Bearer tu_token
